             was indicted for <rs id="t18310908-352-off1807" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-off1807" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-off1807" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18310908-352-cd1808" type="crimeDate">6th of July</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-352-off1807 t18310908-352-cd1808"></join>, 1 coat, value 10s.; 1 pair of breeches, value 7s.; 1 pair of trousers, value 3s., and 2 waistcoats, value 4s.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               
                  <persName id="t18310908-352-victim2515" type="victimName">
                     Henry Hart 
                     Hart
                  <interp inst="t18310908-352-victim2515" type="surname" value="Hart"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-victim2515" type="given" value="Henry Hart"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-victim2515" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-352-off1807 t18310908-352-victim2515"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>HENRY HART HART. I <rs id="t18310908-352-viclabel1809" type="occupation">keep a sale-shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-352-victim2515 t18310908-352-viclabel1809"></join> in Monmouth-street. The prisoner lodged in my house - I was at Mr. Goodman's. in Holywell-street, on the 6th of July, and saw a coat there, which I recognized as mine.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-352-person2516">
                  ABRAHAM 
                  GOODMAN
               <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2516" type="surname" value="GOODMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2516" type="given" value="ABRAHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2516" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I keep a shop in Holywell-street. The prisoner sold me this coat on the 6th of July, for 10s. 6d., and told me his brother had bought it in Mon<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183109080148"></xptr>mouth-street - that it was much too large for him - that he went to exchange it, and they wanted so much more money he would not give it; he gave his address, "
               <persName id="t18310908-352-person2517">
                  John 
                  Newman
               <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2517" type="surname" value="Newman"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2517" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2517" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Wardour-street.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BODKIN. Q. Did he not give you that as his brother's address? A. Yes; he did not state that he was going to France.</p>
               <p>HENRY HART HART. I had the prisoner taken - he said he knew nothing about it; the officer searched him, and found the duplicates - he then said he did it from distress, and hoped I would forgive him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-352-person2518">
                  GEORGE 
                  AVIS
               <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2518" type="surname" value="AVIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2518" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2518" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I found these four duplicates on the prisoner - I heard him state what Mr. Hart has mentioned.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-352-person2519">
                  GEORGE 
                  KING
               <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2519" type="surname" value="KING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2519" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2519" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker. I have a pair of trousers and two waistcoats - the trousers and one waistcoat were pawned by a man, and one waistcoat, for 1s. 6d. was pawned by a woman; the duplicates the officer found were given for them.</p>
               <p>MR. HART. I know these things are all mine.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Are they not what you deal in? A. Yes; Coben serves in my shop - I have another shop about twenty houses off, where 
               <persName id="t18310908-352-person2520">
                  Moses 
                  Solomon
               <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2520" type="surname" value="Solomon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2520" type="given" value="Moses"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2520" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             serves- they keep to their own shops; the prisoner said he knew nothing about Mr. Goodman, or the coat - I am sure he did not say he knew nothing about the purchase of it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-352-person2521">
                  HENRY 
                  COHEN
               <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2521" type="surname" value="COHEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2521" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2521" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am shopman to Mr. Hart. and reside at the house at which the prisoner lodges. This coat was in the shop, and had not been sold.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q.It might not have been sold by you, but whether Solomon had been there, and sold it, you cannot tell? A. I had it in my hand the day before the prisoner was taken; this has a private-mark on the collar.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-352-person2522">
                  BENJAMIN 
                  TIMMS
               <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2522" type="surname" value="TIMMS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2522" type="given" value="BENJAMIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-person2522" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker. I produce a pair of breeches, but do not know who pawned them - this is the duplicate I gave.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. My brother was going to France; I recommended him to a shop, where he bought several articles, but as he had more luggage than he could carry he gave me the coat to sell - he said he had been to where he bought it, and they would not allow him any thing like the money he gave; it had been bought four weeks previous to my being taken.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310908-352-verdict1810" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-verdict1810" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 23. - <rs id="t18310908-352-punish1811" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310908-352-punish1811" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-352-defend2513 t18310908-352-punish1811"></join>
               Confined Six Months
            </rs>.</p>
